abstract: You got your beautiful Python code running on your computer and you want to share it with a world. In this talk talk I'll step by step in fastest way possible to get your code running on AWS as cheap as possible and give you advice on how to scale it when time comes.
Main goal is to push your code to github repo, grab a cup of tea/coffee while your pipeline do your work and return to your changes running on cloud.
